<HEAD>Police: Palestinian Killed Jewish Teen Who Dreamed Of Co-Existence</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> teen-ager who dreamed of Jewish-Arab co-existence and befriended many Arabs in the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> was slain by a <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> acquaintance after she refused to get him a gun, police said Wednesday. The Palestinian, whose name was not released, confessed to the slaying of 18-year-old <PERSON> Ziva </PERSON> <PERSON> Goldovsky </PERSON> and reconstructed the crime for police, said investigator <PERSON> Uri </PERSON> <PERSON> Weisskoop </PERSON>. Ms. <PERSON> Goldovsky </PERSON>'s charred remains were found Aug. 15 in a field near the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> town <LOCATION> El </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bireh </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Weisskoop </PERSON> said her assailant choked her from behind and struck her repeatedly with a large stone before he and an accomplice set the corpse on fire. Ms. <PERSON> Goldovsky </PERSON> became the fifth Israeli to die in the 9-month-old Palestinian uprising. The Palestinian death toll has reached 259. <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> radio described Ms. <PERSON> Goldovsky </PERSON>, an immigrant from the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>, as an activist in the left-wing <ORGANIZATION> Mapam </ORGANIZATION> party `` who could be found at most pro-Palestinian demonstrations.'' Ms. <PERSON> Goldovsky </PERSON>, a resident of the <LOCATION> Tel </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Aviv </LOCATION> suburb of Holon, was engaged to a Palestinian from the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> city of <LOCATION> Hebron </LOCATION>, friends of the victim told <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> last month. Ms. <PERSON> Goldovsky </PERSON>'s fiance, who has a police record, is in custody on robbery charges but is not a suspect in the slaying, police said. On Aug. 13, Ms. <PERSON> Goldovsky </PERSON> and a Palestinian acquaintance went for a walk near <LOCATION> El </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bireh </LOCATION> and began to argue, <ORGANIZATION> Israel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> radio </ORGANIZATION> said. The man started hitting her and shouted: `` Why do you dress so immodestly?'' the report said. `` Do n't hit me,'' she said. `` Even my parents do n't beat me.'' The man then accused her of being an informer for <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s <PERSON> Shin </PERSON> <PERSON> Bet </PERSON> security service. When she denied this, he said: `` Prove it, get me a pistol.'' She refused, saying: `` I should get you a gun so you can kill young Jewish boys and girls?'' The man again slapped Ms. <PERSON> Goldovsky </PERSON> and then choked her. `` He took us to the place where he killed her,'' <PERSON> Weisskoop </PERSON> was quoted as telling the radio. `` He approached her from behind, choked her and laid her on the ground. `` Then he hit her with a large stone. About 50 yards from the site of the killing he and a friend burned the body and this is how she was found.'' One of Ms. <PERSON> Goldovsky </PERSON>'s Jewish friends, speaking on condition of anonymity, said last month she often hitchhiked to the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and formed friendships with many Palestinians. The friend said Ms. <PERSON> Goldovsky </PERSON> dreamed of Jewish-Arab co-existence. `` <PERSON> Ziva </PERSON> would have continued her road of co-existence even if she knew what her end would be,'' he said.
