rom Sikhs in the last car and killed eight Hindus by firing at point-blank range. Two Sikh passengers died later after being caught in cross fire between the extremists and security forces. `` There were 35 passengers in the last car, about half Hindus. We all could have been dead, had the security forces not come in our rescue,'' said <PERSON> Singh </PERSON>, a Hindu. Under government order, trains in <LOCATION> Punjab </LOCATION> carry security forces to thwart possible Sikh terrorist attacks. Militant Sikhs have been fighting since 1982 for a separate homeland in <LOCATION> Punjab </LOCATION> state. More than 1,850 people have died this year in violence blamed on the militants. Sikhs, who make up 2 percent of <LOCATION> India </LOCATION>'s 800 million people, allege they are discriminated against by <PERSON> Hindus </PERSON>, who comprise about 80 percent of the population. Sikhs are a majority in <LOCATION> Punjab </LOCATION>.
