he wrote, `` all such materials deposited with the university shall become from that date the absolute property of <ORGANIZATION> Boston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION>.'' Mrs. <PERSON> King </PERSON>, however, claims her husband had privately indicated his wish that the archive be stored permanently in the South.
