ficials required eligibility hearings for all new voter registration applicants. <PERSON> Rajneesh </PERSON>'s feisty personal secretary, <PERSON> Ma </PERSON> <PERSON> Anand </PERSON> <PERSON> Sheela </PERSON>, is in federal prison on a variety of convictions stemming from her conduct at the commune. Among other crimes, she was convicted of poisoning salad bars in nearby The <LOCATION> Dalles </LOCATION>, causing more than 750 people to become ill; giving glasses of poisoned water to county officials, and setting fire to the county planning office. <PERSON> Rajneesh </PERSON>, 56, returned to <LOCATION> India </LOCATION> in 1985 after pleading guilty to federal immigration charges. As part of a plea agreement, he received a suspended 10-year sentence, paid a $ 400,000 fine and agreed not to return to the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> for five years without the written permission of the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> attorney general. He now lectures and meditates at a commune in <LOCATION> Pune </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> India </LOCATION>. The commune disbanded after the guru's departure. The property is scheduled for auction next month under foreclosure proceedings. <LOCATION> Wasco </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> residents have expressed concern about the weekend gathering, but <PERSON> Sheriff </PERSON> <PERSON> Art </PERSON> <PERSON> Labrousse </PERSON> said he expects no trouble. `` We're just going to be business as usual,'' he said.
