<HEAD>Energy Department Asks For Nuclear Waste Dump Approval</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> urged <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> on Thursday to give speedy approval to legislation allowing the government to open in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> the nation's first permanent dump for radioactive garbage resulting from nuclear weapons production. But Rep. <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Richardson </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-N.M. </LOCATION>, said he will insist that the Waste Isolation Pilot Plant, or WIPP, meet standards still being developed by the <ORGANIZATION> Environmental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Protection </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> before any nuclear trash is stored at the 10,000-acre site east of <LOCATION> Carlsbad </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Troy </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Wade </PERSON> <PERSON> II </PERSON>, acting assistant energy secretary for defense programs, countered that limited storage of nuclear wastes is necessary for an experimental five-year period to help scientists determine compliance with <ORGANIZATION> EPA </ORGANIZATION> regulations. <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Guimond </PERSON>, director of the <ORGANIZATION> EPA </ORGANIZATION>'s office of radiation programs, agreed, saying experimental storage would `` better information to make that determination.'' <PERSON> Richardson </PERSON> said there is no way the WIPP facility can begin receiving the first of 210,000 tons of radioactive trash by next month's target date, because the steel containers for transporting the wastes have proved unsatisfactory in performance tests. <PERSON> Wade </PERSON> said tests of a redesigned container are nearing completion, and certification is expected before the end of the year. <PERSON> Richardson </PERSON> presided over a <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORG