nturies and its turning up in <LOCATION> France </LOCATION> in 1354. In 1389, the shroud was denounced as a forgery by Bishop <PERSON> Pierre </PERSON> <PERSON> d'Arcis </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Troyes </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>, who said in a letter that his predecessor knew who painted it. The painter's name does not appear in any known document.
