35,300. A 1934 costume design for a <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION> theater by <PERSON> Erte </PERSON>, pseudonym of <PERSON> Romain </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Tirtoff </PERSON>, sold to a private collector for $ 27,000, a record for the artist's work. Fantasy paintings by the living German artist <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Wunderlich </PERSON> also did well, one called `` Olympia with Leaf,'' based on <PERSON> Edouard </PERSON> <PERSON> Manet </PERSON>'s famous nude courtesan, `` Olympia,'' sold for $ 26,000.
