tances of bacterium-related disease. `` I have trouble puting a lot of weight on the <LOCATION> Minnesota </LOCATION> study,'' said <PERSON> Harrison </PERSON>. <PERSON> Mortimer </PERSON> said the newer vaccine has been shown to create more antibodies in younger children, so `` the probable benefits outweigh the costs and risks, if any, -LRB- and -RRB- I recommend use of this -LRB- new -RRB- vaccine for children beginning at 18 months of age, pending further information.''
