<HEAD>LaserPhotos SPB1,2,3</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By PAT LEISNER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BRADENTON, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Half of the 1,000 people forced from their homes by waist-deep water headed home Thursday as floodwaters subsided, leaving roads passable and letting businesses and schools reopen. Scattered showers continued Thursday, but <LOCATION> Manatee </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> was spared the torrential downpours of the previous three days that turned streets into rivers. All but one school reopened Thursday. Damage in the rain-soaked Bradenton-Palmetto area of <LOCATION> Tampa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bay </LOCATION> was estimated at more than $ 1 million. The area has been drenched by more than 14 inches of rain this week. Gov. <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Martinez </PERSON> planned to view the area by helicopter on Friday. `` The heavy rains and flooding have caused a severe dispruption in the lives of <LOCATION> Manatee </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> residents and I want to see firsthand whether condiions might require additional assistance from the state,'' he said. The flooding was blamed on a near-stationary cold front hovering across the central <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> peninsula. The <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Weather </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> said the front Thursday was drifting north to the Tampa-St. <LOCATION> Petersburg </LOCATION> area, where the <ORGANIZATION> Red </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cross </ORGANIZATION> opened two shelters for possible evacuees from low-lying areas The steady rains were expected to fade to occasional showers and thunderstorms overnight. Floodwaters Wednesday swept away a motorist and drowned a toddler, authorities said. <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Mercer </PERSON>, 45, was pulled under by a strong current in a drainage ditch and presumed drowned. He disappeared after a car stalled in the ditch and began to float. In <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Port </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Richey </LOCATION>, 2-year-old