<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The belief that the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>' economic standing in the world will be rescued by emerging high-technology industries is being questioned by a prestigious study group which said the country is fast losing its dominance in many of these fields. The Council on Competitiveness recommended Wednesday a major effort on the part of government, industry and schools to reverse the trend. `` We can not afford any further erosion in our once-commanding technological lead,'' said the council's report.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> has agreed to sell all 76 of its Gold Circle and <PERSON> Richway </PERSON> stores for more than $ 325 million, the Toronto-based retailing and real estate company said. The buyer, <ORGANIZATION> Kimco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Development </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, a privately-held owner and manager of shopping centers, said Wednesday it had agreed to sell 31 of the stores to <ORGANIZATION> Dayton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hudson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and to leas 35 to <ORGANIZATION> Hills </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stores </ORGANIZATION> and two to K mart <ORGANIZATION> Corp </ORGANIZATION>. Buyers or operators are still being sought for the other eight stores, according to <ORGANIZATION> Kimco </ORGANIZATION>, which is based in <LOCATION> Roslyn </LOCATION>, N.Y.
