<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Whether driving a run-of-the-mill station wagon or an expensive luxury car, the safest vehicles generally are the largest, accordinbg to an insurance industry report. The report released Wednesday on injury claims involving 207 popular cars showed a wide range, as cars with the worst safety record posted injury losses more than double those with the best record. The annual report released by the <ORGANIZATION> Highway </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Loss </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Data </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION>, an insurance industry research group, reflects findings similar to those in previous years.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 More than two dozen women's groups have launched a campaign for legislation requiring large employers to grant unpaid leave to parents of newborn or seriously ill children. `` If politicians truly want to capture women's votes, they must go beyond pro-family rhetoric and photo opportunities with children,'' <PERSON> Judith </PERSON> <PERSON> Lichtman </PERSON>, president of the Women's Legal Defense Fund, said Wednesday. The groups, ranging from <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Women </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> to the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Abortion </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rights </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Action </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> League </ORGANIZATION>, have mobilized in support of the Family and Medical Leave Act tentatively scheduled for a <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> vote Sept. 14.
