<FIRST>u f PM-S&amp;LCrisis 1stLd-Writethru f0021 09-08 0732</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-S&amp;L Crisis, 1st Ld-Writethru, f0021,0749</SECOND>
<HEAD>$2 Billion S&amp;L Bailout Under Fire</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: Top 12 grafs new with today's hearing, edits throughout to
tighten; Also moved on general newswires</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By DAVE SKIDMORE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Members of the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Banking </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> today criticized regulators' use of promissory notes to rescue insolvent savings institutions as a `` shell game'' designed to push the problem into the next administration. The <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Loan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION>, which regulates the nation's 3,000 savings institutions, has pledged more than $ 12 billion over the last three weeks to rescue or close 48 savings institutions, including 21 in <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> and 14 in <LOCATION> Oklahoma </LOCATION>, states hard hit by the depression in the oil industry However, much of the assistance has been in the form of interest-bearing notes, which will obligate the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Savings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Loan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Insurance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> to billions of dollars in payments a year for the next decade. The plan `` seems to be nothing more than a massive shell game in which insolvent institutions are reshuffled, the names changed, and little if any real capital injected, resulting in thinly capitalized weak institutions,'' said Rep. <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Schumer </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-N.Y. </LOCATION> `` Many of these institutions will ultimately have to be bailed out again at even greater cost to the taxpayer,'' he said. <PERSON> Schumer </PERSON> said the bank board's strategy would `` postpone the day on which the bill for this crisis becomes due until long after the members of the current administration have left <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> and are sitting on a beach somewhere.'' However, <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Danny </PERSON> <PERSON> Wall </PERSON>, who is asking <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> to put the full faith and credit of the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> government behind the notes, said the notes, because they are tax free and carry a low interest rate, are the most effective way to close down insolvent thrift institutions that are draining the industry's health Wall said his agency had $ 10.1 billion in the notes outstanding at the end of August and said by the end of this month it will have spent billions more to resolve the cases of 65 more ailing thrifts. Rep. <PERSON> Fernand </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> St </PERSON> <PERSON> Germain </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-R.I. </LOCATION>, chairman of the committee, was particularly critical of the $ 2 billion rescue earlier this week of <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Savings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Loan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Stockton </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif </LOCATION>. The <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Bass </PERSON> <PERSON> Group </PERSON>, the investment arm of a <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Worth </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, billionaire, is spending $ 550 million and getting $ 2 billion in assistance from <ORGANIZATION> FSLIC </ORGANIZATION> to acquire American. It is the largest-ever rescue of a single savings institution. Part of the deal allows Bass to use $ 1.5 billion of <LOCATION> American </LOCATION>'s funds for merchant banking activities such as acquisitions of commercial companies `` Frankly, I am concerned when notes ... are utilized to promote risky ventures such as merchant bank subsidiaries,'' <ORGANIZATION> St </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Germain </ORGANIZATION> said, warning thatr, `` the industry as a whole can be expected to take this as a green light to again reach for the riskier operations.'' The Bass group has been an active player in corporate takeover battles in recent years. It is currently pushing a $ 1.75 billion offer for <ORGANIZATION> Macmillan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a publishing company. Previously, it has participated in buyouts of <ORGANIZATION> Taft </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Howell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. Wall, in a letter earlier this week to Sen. <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> W. </PERSON> <PERSON> Riegle </PERSON>, D-Mich., who also had questioned the merchant banking activities, said they are being permitted to allow the Bass group to `` capture substantial tax benefits'' of taking over the ailing S & amp; L. He noted that 75 percent of the benefits will be funneled back to the government fund insuring S & amp; L Moreover, <PERSON> Wall </PERSON> said, the agreement with <PERSON> Bass </PERSON> `` will impose substantial restrictions, more stringent than those imposed by -LRB- <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> -RRB- state law.'' Some members of <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> fear that the slew of <ORGANIZATION> FSLIC </ORGANIZATION> notes issued in recent weeks setting up the insurance fund for a bailout by taxpayers, with some private analysts pegging the cost of restoring the industry's health as high as $ 80 billion. However, the bank board says it expects to receive $ 42 billion in income over the next decade and to spend only $ 31 billion. The bank board is also being criticized for agreeing to negotiate exclusively with Bass since April 21. Before that, <ORGANIZATION> First </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nationwide </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> San </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Francisco-