Live cattle were .10 cent to .50 cent lower with October at 71.67 cents a pound; feeder cattle were .15 cent to .55 cent lower with September at 81.10 cents a pound; hogs were .32 cent lower to .10 cent higher with October at 38.10 cents a pound; frozen pork bellies were .27 cent to .75 cent lower with February at 47.35 cents a pound. Livestock and meat futures closed higher on Wednesday.
