<HEAD>EEC Warns Japan About Trade Imbalances</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> European </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Economic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Community </ORGANIZATION>'s external trade commissioner warned <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> Thursday to help reduce trade imbalances as the <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> becomes a more important market for <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> <PERSON> Willie </PERSON> <PERSON> De </PERSON> <PERSON> Clercq </PERSON>, in a speech delivered to a journalists' conference in <LOCATION> Berlin </LOCATION> and distributed in <LOCATION> Brussels </LOCATION>, said the unified European market may have to adopt rules to protect some industries from excessive imports However, <PERSON> De </PERSON> <PERSON> Clercq </PERSON> brushed aside fears that the <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> would become more protectionist as it moves to set up a single internal market by 1992 as `` totally unjustified.'' The trade commissioner predicted that <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s surplus with the <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> will increase in the second half of 1988, even though it slipped during the first half of the year. <PERSON> De </PERSON> <PERSON> Clercq </PERSON>, who makes such warnings to <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> on a regular basis, repeated calls for <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> to increase imports and to give the <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> greater access to its markets. He said the issue was becoming more important as the <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> becomes a more important trading partner for <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>. `` The <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> is now the big, profitable, open market for <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>,'' he said. He noted that the creation of a single market will create unified EEC rules on trade and this will benefit foreign companies resident in the <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION>. He warned at the same time that restrictions at the <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> level may be set up in certain `` sensitive sectors'' to replace various national restrictions which currently exist to protect some industries. `` Such community measures would, of course, be discussed with our trading partners and would have to conform fully with our international obligations,'' he said. <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s trade surplus with the 12-nation trade bloc rose in July to 258 billion yen, up 14 percent from the year-earlier period, according to figures distributed Thursday by the <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION>. Calculated in dollars, the surplus rose in July by 28.5 percent to $ 1.9 billion, but fell 3.2 percent in the first seven months of 1988 compared with the year-earlier period. The statistics showed Japanese imports from the <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> rose 16.2 percent in yen terms and by 30.7 percent in dollar terms in the month of July. Non-ferrous metals, aircraft and textiles showed the sharpest growth. Meanwhile, Japanese exports to the <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> rose 15.1 percent in yen terms and 29.6 percent in dollar terms due primarily to increases in exports of automobiles, office machinery and audio-visual equipment.
